Casual workers and volunteers from various departments in Kisumu have been rendered jobless following a directive from the county government that they be relieved of their duties with immediate effect. This is according to a memo dated June 20 addressed to all the chief officers, city manager, the medical superintendent of Jaramogi Oginga Odinga Teaching and Referral Hospital and Kisumu County Hospital. The memo by county secretary Olango Onudi with the subject of termination of casual workers and volunteers stated that the casuals should be terminated with immediate effect. Onudi stated that provision under the countyâ€™s Employment Act and other labour regulations necessitate that casuals are not engaged for a period exceeding three months. Click here for the latest political news   